&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frailty Case Manager, Intermediate Care Team Band 6&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2 WTE 37.5hrs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Place based Locality teams are well established within Walsall with a fully integrated domiciliary service and excellent relationships with Social Services and the Acute Sector.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to develop your role as a Frailty Case Manger meeting demand of the New Ambition for Older People –Standard 7 high level of performance indicators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a multidisciplinary/ Multi Agency Team and have responsibility for a varied caseload of clients in their own homes across the borough, working under the direction of the Clinical Team Leader. You will be working Older People’s Services to develop and support this client group to remain in their homes with enhanced services. You will need to work flexibly to meet the demands of the service and be able to work effectively with partnership agencies such as the private care provider, GP’S.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to operate flexible working practices wherever possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDonna RobertsAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal discussion about the post please contact Donna Roberts . 01922 604920 option 6&lt;/p&gt;
